  "about": {
    "num": "About",
    "title": [
      "I don't start from technology. ",
      {
        "em": "I start from a problem"
      },
      "."
    ],
    "p1": [
      "Before I ask \"what should I build this with,\" I ask \"what's the real problem, and what actually needs to be built to solve it.\" ",
      {
        "em": "That's"
      },
      " where the value is - in the decisions, not in the layer I write code in. Once that's clear, I can build it end-to-end on my own (React, TypeScript, Node, PostgreSQL), down to the details users feel: timing, motion, empty states, and the choices that make a product feel natural."
    ],
    "p2": "When I take a feature, I take it all the way - I'm accountable for getting it shipped, working, and actually solving what it's meant to. That means leading the decisions, closing the gaps with Design, Backend, and QA, and not stopping at the line of \"I wrote my part of the code.\"",
